FT  13 JUL 94 / UK Company News: Tamaris improves further to Pounds 8,000
Tamaris, the nursing home operator, continued its recovery with pre-tax
profits of Pounds 8,000 for the year to March 31, against losses of Pounds
50,000. It reported a profit of Pounds 2,000 at the interim stage.
Mr William Fitch, chairman, said that the reputation of the company's homes
had been enhanced leading to increased occupancy levels and improved
operating profits.
During the year the company raised Pounds 1.2m in a placing and open offer
and a capital reconstruction which resulted in the company moving from a
negative to a net worth.
Turnover rose from Pounds 3.38m to Pounds 3.47m. Earnings per share were
0.03p, against losses of 1.45p.
